            <title>[SOLR-4187] CachingDirectoryFactory NPE on release</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4187</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Likely related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4171&quot; title=&quot;CachingDirectoryFactory should not return any directories after it has been closed.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4171&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4171&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3911&quot; title=&quot;Make Directory and DirectoryFactory first class so that the majority of Solr&amp;#39;s features work with any custom implementations.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3911&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3911&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. This occurs only on today&apos;s check out and not on all nodes just like my comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2529&quot; title=&quot;DIH update trouble with sql field name &amp;quot;pk&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-2529&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-2529&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The stack trace is only part the trace for opening a new searcher. The problem does not disappear after restarting the node.&lt;/p&gt;

